To produce a new openjpeg release (Win32, Linux or OSX):
[replace '1.5' with the current version number, eg '1.5.1']

1. Generate the CHANGES for the release:

$ ./genchange.sh

copy the branch

$ svn copy https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/branches/openjpeg-2.0 https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/tags/version.2.0
$ svn add CHANGES ../../tags/version.2.0
$ svn commit

2. Generates the source tarball + binary tarball (OSX package on Mac):

$ ./release.sh

If you have a windows box, from a CMD console:

> release.bat


